  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Rating systems are intended to guide consumer choices. This project will determine if a
      previously developed scale that evaluates the &quot;healthiness&quot; of a restaurant is correlated
      with the actual choices consumers make when they patronize the restaurants. The study will
      also assess whether a restaurant marketed as &quot;healthy&quot; (Subway) rates higher on this scale
      than another restaurant that makes no such claims (McDonald's). Finally, the investigators
      will compare the calorie purchases from these two restaurants among youths and their families
      who eat at each of the restaurants.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
